Preheat your oven to 200°C. Trim the @radishes{100} and thinly slice. Trim the @carrot{1}. Use a #vegetable peeler{} to peel long ribbons from all sides of the length of the carrot. Stop when you get to the centre, discard the centre. Trim the @cucumber{1/2}. Use a vegetable peeler to peel long ribbons from all sides of the length of the cucumber. Stop when you get to the seedy centre, discard the centre. Pop the radishes, carrot and cucumber in a large #bowl{} and set aside for later. Halve the @burger buns{2}, trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then separate the leaves.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{1}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Sprinkle over the @sesame seeds{15}, toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the wedges nicely spread out.

Put the @mayonnaise{2} in a small bowl with the @korma curry paste{50%g} and @honey{15%g}. Mix together and set aside.

Put the @rice vinegar{30%ml} and @ginger puree{1} in a small bowl. Add the @sugar{1/2} and @olive oil{1}. Season with salt and pepper and mix with a #fork{}. Set aside - dressing made!

Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} in a large bowl and season with salt and pepper. Mix together.

Pop the @cornflour{50%g} in another large bowl and add the @water{50%ml}. Add the @ground ginger{1} and the @soy sauce{12.5%ml}. Season with salt and pepper and whisk with a fork until well combined.

Heat approx 2cm of @oil{1} in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

> You want the oil to be nice and hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

While the oil gets hot, dip one piece of @British chicken thighs{4} in the cornflour mixture so it's completely covered on both sides. Then dip it in the breadcrumbs to coat on both sides. Pop on a #plate{} and repeat with the other chicken thighs.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Once the oil is hot, carefully lay the chicken in the pan and fry until golden brown on each side and cooked through, ~{14-16%minutes} total, turn with #tongs{} every ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Careful not to burn yourself on the hot oil. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Once cooked, remove the chicken to a plate covered in #kitchen roll{}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Pop the burger buns in the oven to warm through for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the dressing to the radish, carrot and cucumber and toss to coat. Spread a spoonful of the katsu mayo on the top and bottom of the burger buns and serve with a couple of baby gem leaves and the chicken thighs inside. Add the remaining leaves to the salad, toss together.

Serve with the wedges and salad alongside with any remaining katsu mayo for dipping your chips in. Enjoy!